Fix: "Add to Home Screen" launches a 404

The web app manifest sets start_url to "./index.html". Because the app is served
under the base path /urban-carnivore-spotter and uses client-side routing, the
launch URL resolves to /urban-carnivore-spotter/index.html — a path the router
has no route for, so the installed PWA / iOS home-screen icon opens the app's
"not found" page.

Changing start_url to "." makes it resolve to the app root
(/urban-carnivore-spotter/), which the router renders normally.

--- a/public/manifest.json
+++ b/public/manifest.json
@@ -8,7 +8,7 @@
       "type": "image/x-icon"
     }
   ],
-  "start_url": "./index.html",
+  "start_url": ".",
   "display": "standalone",
   "theme_color": "#000000",
   "background_color": "#ffffff"
 }

Notes:
- "." is resolved relative to the manifest URL
  (/urban-carnivore-spotter/manifest.json), giving /urban-carnivore-spotter/.
  "/urban-carnivore-spotter/" (absolute) also works and is more explicit.
- To have the installed icon open the report form instead of the map, use
  "start_url": "./reports/create".
